(31, 1, '2018-02-01 08:49:00', '2018-02-01 08:49:00', '<p class=\"red-text\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">The 2011 data of Indian Population estimates 1,241,491,960 people (Source: World Bank)</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">The 2011 census put the Indian Minorities a little above 20% of the total population.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">But for the first time the census does not specifically talk of religious minorities.</span>\r\n(Ref: <a href=\"http://censusindia.gov.in/2011-prov-results/indiaatglance.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">http://censusindia.gov.in/2011-prov-results/indiaatglance.html</a>)\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">The following data is based on 2001 Census</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class=\"populate-table\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Name of Religion</th>\r\n<th>Percentage of total population</th>\r\n<th>Sex ratio</th>\r\n<th>Number of people</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tfoot>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>India</td>\r\n<td>100</td>\r\n<td>933</td>\r\n<td>102.9 crore</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tfoot>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Hindus</td>\r\n<td>80.5</td>\r\n<td>931</td>\r\n<td>82.8 crore</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Muslims</td>\r\n<td>13.4</td>\r\n<td>936</td>\r\n<td>13.8 crore</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Christians</td>\r\n<td>2.3</td>\r\n<td>1009</td>\r\n<td>2.4 crore</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Sikhs</td>\r\n<td>1.9</td>\r\n<td>893</td>\r\n<td>1.96 crore</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Buddhists</td>\r\n<td>0.8</td>\r\n<td>953</td>\r\n<td>0.9 crore</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Jains</td>\r\n<td>0.4</td>\r\n<td>940</td>\r\n<td>0.43 crore</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Other religions</td>\r\n<td>0.6</td>\r\n<td>992</td>\r\n<td>0.62 crore</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n[accordion]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Andhra Pradesh\"]<strong>Capital: Hyderabad (The capital city has 44.59% minority population)</strong>\r\n<strong>Population : 76210007</strong>\r\n\r\nMinority Population in AP : 8373356\r\n\r\nMajority : 6,78,36,651[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Arunachal Pradesh\"]<strong>Capital: Itanagar\r\nPopulation 1,382,611</strong>\r\n\r\nMinority Population: Deeply Divided Population\r\n\r\nHindu: 379,935 (34.6%), The Animists mostly Donyi Polo: 337,399 (30.7%), Christian: 205,548 (18.7%), Buddhist: 143,028 (13.0%), Muslim: 20,675 (1.9%), Sikh: 1,865 (0.1%), Jain: 216 (0.1%)[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Assam\"]<strong>Capital: Dispur\r\nPopulation 31,169,272</strong>\r\n\r\nMinority Population: 9331704 (29%)[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Bihar\"]<strong>Capital: Patna\r\nPopulation 103,804,637</strong>\r\n\r\nMinority Population : 19% of the total population\r\n(Muslims constitute 18.5% and others 0.5)[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Chhattisgarh\"]<strong>Capital: Raipur</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Goa\"]<strong>Capital: Panjim</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Gujarat\"]<strong>Capital: Gandhinagar\r\nPopulation 60,439,692</strong>\r\nMinority Population: 10.9% minorities (9.06% muslims, 0.5% Christians, 1.03 % Christians, 0.19 % Sikhs, 0.07% Buddhists and .05 % others)\r\n[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Haryana\"]<strong>Capital: Chandigarh (shared, Union Territory)\r\nPopulation 25,353,081</strong>\r\nMinority Population: Sikhs 6%, Muslims 5.78% (mainly Meos muslim who are the ethnic group of Mewat districts), Others 0.45%.\r\n[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Himachal Pradesh\"]<strong>Capital: Shimla\r\nPopulation 6,856,509</strong>\r\n\r\nMinority Population: 4.53 % (2001 Census)\r\n(Muslims account for 1.97%, Sikhs 1.19%, Buddhists 1.25%, and Christians 0.13%)\r\n\r\n(The freedom of Religion Act, 2006 enacted by the Legislative Assembly of Himachal Pradesh, received the assent of the Governor on February 18, 2007. The National Commission for Minorities has examined the provisions of the Act and the Statement of Objects and Reasons. The latter refers to \"rise in conversions based on allurement generally\" and to \"a persistent demand from across the different strata of the society, urging the State Government to curb it\" as, otherwise, it may \"erode the confidence and mutual trust between the different religious and ethnic groups in the State\")\r\n[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Jammu and Kashmir\"]<strong>Capital: Srinagar (summer), Jammu (winter)\r\nPopulation 12,548,926</strong>\r\n\r\nJammu: Hindus constitute 65%, Muslims 31% and Sikhs, 4% of the population.\r\nLadakh: (comprises of Buddhists-dominated Leh and Muslim-dominated Kargil)\r\nBuddhists 46% , Muslims 47% and Hindus constitute 6% of the population.\r\n\r\nThe people of Ladakh are of Indo-Tibetan origin, while the southern Jammu includes many communities tracing their ancestry to the nearby Indian states of Haryana and Punjab and Delhi.\r\n\r\nIn the whole of the state of J&amp; K Muslims constitute 67%, Hindus 30%, Buddhists 1% and the Sikhs 2% of the population.\r\n[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Jharkhand\"]<strong>Capital: Ranchi</strong>\r\n[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Karnataka\"]<strong>Capital: Bangalore</strong>\r\n[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Kreala\"]<strong>Capital: Thiruvananthapuram</strong>\r\n[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Madhya Pradesh\"]<strong>Capital: Bhopal</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Maharashtra\"]<strong>Capital: Mumbai</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Manipur\"]<strong>Capital: Imphal</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Meghalaya\"]<strong>Capital: Shillong</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Mizoram\"]<strong>Capital: Aizawl</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Nagaland\"]<strong>Capital: Kohima</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Odisha (Orissa)\"]<strong>Capital: Bhubaneswar</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Punjab\"]<strong>Capital: Chandigarh (shared, Union Territory)</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Sikkim\"]<strong>Capital: Gangtok</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Tamil Nadu\"]<strong>Capital: Chennai</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Tripura\"]<strong>Capital: Agartala</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Uttar Pradesh\"]<strong>Capital: Lucknow</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Uttarakhand\"]<strong>Capital: Dehradun (interim)</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"West Bengal\"]<strong>Capital: Kolkata</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[/accordion]\r\n<h3 class=\"headline-divider\">Union Territories</h3>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[accordion]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Andaman and Nicobar Islands\"]<strong>Capital: Port Blair</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Chandigarh\"]<strong>Capital: Chandigarh</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Dadra and Nagar Haveli\"]<strong>Capital: Silvassa</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Daman and Diu\"]<strong>Capital: Daman</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Lakshadweep\"]<strong>Capital: Kavaratti</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n\r\n[accordion-item title=\"National Capital Territory of Delhi\"]<strong>Capital: Delhi</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n\r\n[accordion-item title=\"Puducherry (Pondicherry)\"]<strong>Capital: Pondicherry</strong>[/accordion-item]\r\n[/accordion]', 'States', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'states', '', '', '2018-07-07 11:48:01', '2018-07-07 11:48:01', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wp_theme/?page_id=31', 0, 'page', '', 0),
