(193, 1, '2014-07-31 11:51:19', '2014-07-31 11:51:19', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In fresh controversy keeping up to a majoritarian mindset, BJP legislator K Laxman from Telangana opposing Sania Mirza\'s selection as the brand ambassador of the state called her an \'outsider\' on grounds that \'she was a daughter- in- law of Pakistan\'. Sania 27, is married to Pakistani cricketer Shoaib Malik and continues to play for India. She is presently ranked doubles world number 5 by the WTA.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Adding fuel to Sania\'s \"Being Indian\" controversy Sudhanshu Trivedi another prominent TV face of the BJP peddled another robust majoritarian common sense in a TV debate on the issue. Trivedi asked amusingly \"what would happen to Sania\'s loyalties if India and Pakistan went to war\".</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Fodder for thought for all respectable nationalists!</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">What role should Sania \'the daughter\', play during times of Indo Pak war?</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Did we also think which side will Shoaib Malik be during war? Or is it just for daughters and daughter in laws to prove loyalties.</p>', 'What matters! Daughters or Daughter- in- laws', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-matters-daughters-or-daughter-in-laws', '', '', '2018-08-02 07:58:13', '2018-08-02 07:58:13', '', 0, 'http://dtechsystem.net/dev/?p=193', 0, 'post', '', 0),
